#: src/guides/textobject.md:36
msgid "Queries for textobject based navigation"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/textobject.md:38
msgid ""
"Tree-sitter based navigation in Helix is done using captures in the "
"following order:"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/textobject.md:41
msgid "`object.movement`"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/textobject.md:42
msgid "`object.around`"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/textobject.md:43
msgid "`object.inside`"
msgstr ""

#: src/guides/textobject.md:45
msgid ""
"For example if a `function.around` capture has been already defined for a "
"language in its `textobjects.scm` file, function navigation should also work "
"automatically. `function.movement` should be defined only if the node "
"captured by `function.around` doesn't make sense in a navigation context."
msgstr ""
